#############################################################################
# GAMBIT central scanner plugin description database                        #
#                                                                           #
# GAMBIT will parse this file and try to match the entries                  #
# to the models it has registered. If there are any                         #
# conflicts it will report them, and if any models                          #
# are lacking descriptions those will be reported too.                      #
# This is then merged with internally known information                     #
# to create a centralised database of model information.                    #
# This is found in the file "<insert name here>"                            #
#                                                                           #
# Note: Yaml syntax for multi-line strings is this:                         #
#                                                                           #
#body: |                                                                    #
#  This is a multi-line string.                                             #
#  "special" metacharacters may                                             #
#  appear here. The extent of this string is                                #
#  indicated by indentation.                                                #
#                                                                           #
# You may tell gambit to ignore any new lines with                          #
# #remove_newlines                                                          #
# text                                                                      #
# #dont_remove_newlines                                                     #
#                                                                           #
# Or you can end the ignore scope the a blank line                          #
# #remove_newlines                                                          #
# text                                                                      #
#                                                                           #
# unaffected_text                                                           #
#############################################################################

priors: |
  #remove_newlines
  In gambit, prior are implamented as transformations.  Formally, this can
  be discribed by calculating the inverse CDF. Prior are specified either 
  in the parameters section when a parameter is declared as so ...
  
  parameter:
    prior_type: flat
    range: [0, 1]
    
  #remove_newlines
  Or in the prior section as so ...
  
  my_prior:
    prior_type: flat
    parameters: [model::parameter, ...]
    range: [0, 1]
    
  #remove_newlines
  Listed below are various priors that GAMBIT recognizes seperated into five groups: one dimensional priors (flat, log, sin, cos, tan, cot), multidimensional priors (gaussian, cauchy), same_as (same_as), fixed value (fixed_value), and dummy (dummy)).I

"1dpriors": [flat,log, sin, cos, tan, cot]
"same_as": [same_as]
"ndpriors": [gaussian, cauchy]
"fixed_value": [fixed_value]
"dummy": [dummy]
  
1dpriors: |
  #remove_newlines
  Specifies a one dimensional prior.  Different prior types that fall into this
  catagory are flat (uniform distribution), log (1/x distribution), and trig
  functions (sin, cos, tan, cot).  If same_as, fixed_value and prior_type are not
  specified, a flat prior is assumed.

  Inifile entries:
      range:       specifies the range in the form [low, hi]
      shift (0):   adds the shift value to the parameter 
      scale (1):   multiplies the scale value to the parameter.  If set to "degrees" will convert degrees to radians.

      output_scaled_values (true):  Outputs the scaled parameters if true.  Set to false if "degrees" is specified.

ndpriors: |
  #remove_newlines
  Specifies the a multi-variate prior.  There are two priors of this type -- 
  gaussian and cauchy

  Inifile entries:
      cov:   coveriance matrix
      sigs ([1...]):  specifies the sqrt of the diagonal components of the coveriance matrix. Defaults to 1 if not specified.
      mean ([0...]):  specifies the mean or median.  Defaults to 0 if not specified.

same_as: |
  #remove_newlines
  Specifies that this parameter is the same as another parameter.  This prior
  does not need the prior_type tag
    
  Inifile entries:
      same_as:     parameter that is the same as the current parameter
      shift (0):   adds the shift value to the parameter 
      scale (1):   multiplies the scale value to the parameter 

fixed_value: |
  #remove_newlines
  Sets the parameter to a fixed value that is defined by the fixed_value option.  If a vector is given instead of a single value, the parameter's value will be sequentially set to the inputed values.  This prior does not need the prior_type tag, just the "fixed_value" option.

dummy: | 
  Does absolutly nothing.
